  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study examines the effectiveness of an herbal mouthwash made from salvia in maintaining&#xD;
      good oral health among patients in palliative care. It is hypothesized that using the&#xD;
      mouthwash made from salvia will result in better oral health and more oral comfort than using&#xD;
      with conventional normal saline mouthwash.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to examine the effectiveness of an herbal mouthwash made from salvia&#xD;
      officinalis (SO) in maintaining good oral health among patients in palliative care. The study&#xD;
      compares a mouthwash based on salvia tea solution with conventional normal saline mouthwash&#xD;
      and addresses the following research questions:&#xD;
&#xD;
        1. Does the SO-based mouthwash provide a better treatment than conventional normal saline&#xD;
           in maintaining good oral health in terminally ill patients?&#xD;
&#xD;
        2. Is there a difference in the individual perception of oral comfort in patients receiving&#xD;
           SO versus patients receiving saline rinsing solution?&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
